{{Infobox language family |name=Croisilles |altname=(North) Adelbert Range |region=[[New Guinea]] |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=Northeast New Guinea? |fam2=[[Madang languages|Madang]] |fam3=Central Madang |glotto=croi1234 |glottorefname=Croisilles }}
The '''Croisilles languages''' are a [[language family|family]] of languages in the [[Madang languages|Madang]] stock of New Guinea. The occupy the northern Abelbert Range, vs. the [[Southern Adelbert languages]], another branch of Madang.
