{{otheruses}}
A '''sortie''' (from the French word meaning [[wikt:sortie|''exit'']]) is a deployment or dispatch of one military unit, be it an [[aircraft]], [[ship]], or troops, from a strongpoint.  The sortie, whether by one or more aircraft or vessels, usually has a specific [[Military operation|mission]]. The '''sortie rate''' is the number of sorties that a given unit can support in a given time. The term is an evolution of the concept of "[[sortie (siege warfare)|sortie]]" in [[siege warfare]].

In [[military aviation]], a sortie is a combat mission of an individual aircraft, starting when the aircraft takes off. For example, one mission involving six aircraft would tally six sorties.

